Package org.knime.core.webui.node.dialog.defaultdialog.widget.handler

Interface DependencyHandler<S>

Type Parameters:
S - the settings, the handler is depending on.
All Known Subinterfaces:
ButtonActionHandler<R,S,M>, ButtonUpdateHandler<R,S,M>, ChoicesUpdateHandler<S>, UpdateHandler<R,S>
All Known Implementing Classes:
CancelableActionHandler, CancelableActionHandler.UpdateHandler, DomainChoicesUpdateHandler, NoopButtonUpdateHandler, NoopChoicesUpdateHandler
public interface DependencyHandler<S>
The fields specified in this class have to reference other settings of the current node settings. To reference a setting, use the same name and the same type (for nested settings all names along the way have to match) as the field that is to be referenced. If there is a field which is not unique with respect to its field name and type, use the DeclaringDefaultNodeSettings annotation to further specify the specific node settings class of the field. *

Example: 

            class OtherSettings {
                  // referencing "MyNodeModelSettings#m_foo".
                  @DeclaringDefaultNodeSettings(MyNodeModelSettings.class)
                  String m_bar;
            }

            class MyActionHandler implements DialogDataServiceHandler<String, OtherSettings>

            class MyNodeViewSettings extends DefaultNodeSettings {

                @ButtonWidget(actionHandler = MyActionHandler)
                String m_foo;

                String m_bar;

            }

            class MyNodeModelSettings extends DefaultNodeSettings {
                String m_bar;
            }
For simple scenarios where there is only one DefaultNodeSettings class used and a setting should depend on all other settings, the DefaultNodeSettings class itself can be directly used as the generic class.
